50|$|An {{option is}} the right to convey a piece of property. The person {{granting}} the option is called the optionor (or more usually, the grantor) and the person who has the benefit of the option is called the <b>optionee</b> (or more usually, the beneficiary).|$|E
50|$|In legal conveyancing, {{the grant}} is {{the means by}} which a party conveys title or encumbrance. In trust law, the grant is the act by which the settlor creates the trust for the {{interests}} of the trustee. In an option contract, the right of the <b>optionee</b> to exercise the option is considered a grant {{on the part of the}} optionor. In philanthropy, a donor may provide a grant of money.|$|E

